{
  "texts": [
    "Each regulation is classified as weak or strong based on the type of experiment used to identify the interaction.",
    "For instance, a ChIP analysis with statistical validation is considered to provide stronger evidence than ChIP-chip only or ChIP-sequence analysis.",
    "This section addresses the improvement of the prediction accuracy of genetic interactions using the published literature.",
    "We propose an automated framework involving two Large Language Models (LLM)-BioBERT and BERN2-which are pre-trained on a large corpus of biological data.",
    "The overall architecture of the proposed LLM based framework is presented in two."
  ]
}